snippet.textDisplay: so the thing with these new kygo songs is that they all sound kind of the same, and I don't feel that natural feeling (for example Drums, or the synth in shine remix wich sounds like a flute ) that gave the whole song that kind of different atmosphere , from all the others he did , the sexual healing remix or take on me remix had that same vibe but a totally different sound , and now it just sounds a little bit unlovely made , not really ready, and I miss the detail sounds and the sophistication (in cut your teeth he used so many diffrent organic sounds and combined them in some loops and created with this a kind of tension arc , that is completely lost in this and the newer songs in my opinion.Now its like that super mainstream sound.. there isn't a mix anymore like on cloud 9 (stay ,Happy Birthday, Carry me , Firestone,stole the show ) all with a unique sound and feeling..but the positiv thing in that song is that he didn't chop the vocal and did that vocal melody creation thing , but im very looking forward for the whole album , I hope that he's coming back to his older sound love that one , that's for me the only really tropical house
